defs.name: BiMap
defs.docs: Type definition for convenience and compatibility with older versions of this crate.

defs.name: Neither
defs.docs: Neither the left nor the right value previously existed in the bimap.

defs.name: Left
defs.docs: The left value existed in the bimap, and the previous left-right pair is returned.

defs.name: Right
defs.docs: The right value existed in the bimap, and the previous left-right pair is returned.

defs.name: Pair
defs.docs:
The left-right pair already existed in the bimap, and the previous left-right pair is
 returned.

defs.name: Both
defs.docs:
Both the left and the right value existed in the bimap, but as part of separate pairs. The
 first tuple is the left-right pair of the previous left value, and the second is the
 left-right pair of the previous right value.

defs.name: Overwritten
defs.docs:
The previous left-right pairs, if any, that were overwritten by a call to the
 [`insert`](BiHashMap::insert) method of a bimap.

defs.name: did_overwrite
defs.docs:
Returns a boolean indicating if the `Overwritten` variant implies any values were
 overwritten.
